      "concerns": [
        "Existing uncommented difok lines may remain, leading to duplicate entries that could override the intended value.",
        "No backup of original configuration files is performed before modification.",
        "The sed pattern used to replace commented lines does not handle spaces before the '#' character reliably on all systems.",
        "The script assumes all override files are in /etc/security/pwquality.conf.d/*.conf; variations in distribution layout could miss legacy overrides."
      ],
      "suggested_improvements": [
        "Adjust the sed command to replace both commented and uncommented difok lines, e.g., sed -i -e '/^\\s*#?\\s*difok\\s*=\\s*[^\\n]*$/c\\difok = 1' /etc/security/pwquality.conf.",
        "Add a pre\u2011execution backup: cp /etc/security/pwquality.conf{,.bak} and similarly for each override file.",
        "Verify the system's override directory location and handle cases where multiple directories or nested directories exist.",
        "After modifications, run `pam-auth-update` or reload PAM to ensure changes take effect immediately."
      ],
